('mews', 'Mews', 'Cloud-native property management system for modern hotels and hospitality groups',
 E'Mews is a cloud-native property management system built for hotels, hostels, aparthotels, and multi-property hospitality groups that have outgrown legacy PMS platforms. Unlike traditional property management systems built on Windows-based on-premise software, Mews was designed from the start as a web-based, API-first platform that integrates with the modern hospitality tech stack - revenue management systems, channel managers, payment processors, and guest-facing apps - without custom connectors or expensive middleware.\n\nThe platform covers the full property operations workflow: reservations management, front desk check-in and checkout, housekeeping assignment and status tracking, rate and inventory management, and financial reporting. Mews Payments is the built-in payment processing layer that automates pre-authorisation, deposit collection, and checkout payment without card-on-file risk. The guest-facing side includes a digital check-in flow, in-stay service requests, and digital checkout that allows guests to complete arrival and departure from their phone without visiting the front desk.\n\nMews has built an open marketplace of over 1,000 integrations with point-of-sale systems, spa and activity booking tools, revenue management platforms, and distribution channels. For independent hotels and boutique chains looking to move off legacy Opera or Maestro installations, Mews offers a modern alternative with a substantially faster implementation timeline. The platform is particularly strong for lifestyle hotels, hostels with complex bed and shared-space inventory, and multi-property groups that need a unified view across locations.',
 'https://mews.com', 'https://mews.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.6, 3800, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['hospitality', 'hotel-management', 'travel'],
 ARRAY['Cloud-native architecture with 1,000+ marketplace integrations for modern hotel stacks', 'Mews Payments automates pre-auth, deposits, and checkout without card-on-file friction', 'Digital check-in and checkout app reduces front desk load during peak arrival windows', 'Strong fit for boutique hotels, lifestyle brands, and multi-property groups leaving legacy PMS'],
 ARRAY['Pricing requires a custom quote - no published per-room pricing tier', 'Some advanced reporting and BI features require third-party BI integrations', 'Smaller ecosystem of POS integrations for complex food and beverage operations vs older platforms', 'Migration from legacy PMS requires dedicated project management and training investment'],
 ARRAY['Replacing legacy on-premise PMS at independent hotels and small chains', 'Running digital check-in and check-out to reduce front desk staffing needs', 'Multi-property hospitality groups needing unified operations across locations'],
 NOW()),

('cloudbeds', 'Cloudbeds', 'All-in-one hospitality platform combining PMS, channel manager, and revenue tools',
 E'Cloudbeds is an all-in-one hospitality management platform serving over 22,000 properties globally, combining a property management system, channel manager, booking engine, and revenue management tools in a single subscription. The integrated architecture solves one of the most persistent pain points in small and mid-size hotel operations: maintaining rate and inventory parity across direct bookings, OTA channels (Booking.com, Expedia, Airbnb), and GDS without manual rate syncing or expensive standalone channel management tools.\n\nThe PMS handles reservations, front desk operations, housekeeping, group bookings, and guest communications. Cloudbeds Payments processes cards directly within the platform. The built-in channel manager connects to over 300 distribution channels with two-way XML integrations that update rates and availability in real time when a booking is made on any channel. The booking engine powers the hotel''s direct website with a white-label reservation flow designed to convert lookers into bookers without losing the guest to an OTA.\n\nCloudbeds Intelligence, the platform''s revenue management module, provides market data, competitor rate benchmarking, and demand forecasting to help revenue managers set optimal rates without a separate RMS subscription. For independent hotels, bed and breakfasts, vacation rental properties, and small chains that previously required three or four separate tools to manage operations and distribution, Cloudbeds delivers a consolidated platform at a price point accessible to small operators. The company serves properties in over 150 countries with localised payment, tax, and currency handling.',
 'https://cloudbeds.com', 'https://cloudbeds.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.5, 4200, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['hospitality', 'hotel-management', 'channel-manager'],
 ARRAY['All-in-one PMS, channel manager, and booking engine eliminates multi-tool integration overhead', 'Connects to 300+ distribution channels with real-time two-way rate and inventory sync', 'Cloudbeds Intelligence provides competitor benchmarking and demand forecasting without a separate RMS', 'Serves properties in 150+ countries with localised payment, tax, and currency support'],
 ARRAY['Per-property pricing requires a demo - no self-serve plan for small operators', 'Some advanced revenue management capabilities require the premium Intelligence add-on', 'Mobile app is functional but less polished than best-in-class standalone apps', 'Customer support response times can vary for properties in smaller markets'],
 ARRAY['Independent hotels replacing disconnected PMS and channel manager subscriptions', 'B&Bs and boutique properties managing direct bookings alongside OTA distribution', 'Small hotel chains needing unified rate parity management across properties and channels'],
 NOW()),

('guesty', 'Guesty', 'Property management platform for vacation rental operators and short-term rental hosts',
 E'Guesty is a property management platform built specifically for the short-term rental and vacation rental market - serving professional hosts managing 5 to 5,000 listings on Airbnb, Vrbo, Booking.com, and direct booking channels. Where hotel PMS platforms are designed around traditional room night operations, Guesty is architected for the operational patterns of short-term rentals: flexible pricing, variable cleaning schedules, turnover-day logistics, multi-platform listing management, and guest communication automation across booking channels.\n\nThe unified inbox consolidates all guest messages from Airbnb, Vrbo, Booking.com, and direct bookings into a single thread, with AI-assisted reply suggestions that draft responses based on the guest''s question and the property''s standard information. Automated messaging workflows send check-in instructions, door codes, check-out reminders, and review requests on schedule without manual intervention. The multi-calendar view shows all bookings across all properties and all channels in a single view, with direct editing capability.\n\nGuesty''s dynamic pricing tool adjusts nightly rates based on demand signals, local events, competitor pricing, and occupancy patterns. The operations module handles cleaning team assignment, inspection checklists, and maintenance task tracking tied to checkout events. For professional vacation rental managers and co-hosting businesses operating at scale, Guesty provides the operational infrastructure to run a multi-property portfolio without a proportional increase in administrative staff. Pricing is percentage-based on booking revenue, making it accessible to growing portfolios without large upfront licensing costs.',
 'https://guesty.com', 'https://guesty.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.5, 5100, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['vacation-rentals', 'hospitality', 'channel-manager'],
 ARRAY['Unified inbox consolidates Airbnb, Vrbo, and Booking.com messages with AI-assisted replies', 'Automated guest messaging workflows handle check-in, checkout, and review requests on schedule', 'Multi-calendar view across all properties and channels with direct booking editing', 'Dynamic pricing tool adjusts rates based on demand, events, and competitor pricing automatically'],
 ARRAY['Percentage-of-revenue pricing model can become expensive as portfolio revenue grows', 'Some users report onboarding complexity for large portfolios migrating from other platforms', 'Advanced automation workflows require time investment to configure correctly upfront', 'Customer support quality varies - complex issues may require escalation to account managers'],
 ARRAY['Professional vacation rental managers running 10+ Airbnb and Vrbo listings', 'Co-hosting businesses managing short-term rental portfolios for property owners', 'Short-term rental operators automating guest communications and operations at scale'],
