('duetto', 'Duetto', 'Revenue management platform for hotels using AI to optimise pricing and demand forecasting',
 E'Duetto is the enterprise revenue management system used by major hotel brands, casino hotels, and resort operators to optimise pricing, availability, and distribution strategy using AI-powered demand forecasting. The platform replaces the manual spreadsheet-based rate-setting process that still runs revenue management at many hotels with dynamic, data-driven pricing that updates in real time as demand signals shift.\n\nGameChanger, Duetto''s core pricing engine, generates recommended rates for every room type, booking window, and distribution channel based on a continuous analysis of historical booking patterns, current pickup pace, competitor rates, local events, and macroeconomic demand signals. Rate recommendations can be applied automatically through business rules or reviewed and approved by revenue managers through an approval workflow. The system integrates with the hotel''s PMS, central reservation system, and channel manager to push approved rates to all distribution endpoints without manual entry.\n\nOpen Pricing, Duetto''s pricing philosophy and methodology, prices each room type and booking date independently rather than using the traditional BAR (Best Available Rate) hierarchy where all room types move in fixed increments. This approach captures additional revenue on high-demand dates when guests are willing to pay for specific room type upgrades, and improves occupancy on soft dates by offering targeted discounts without moving all rates simultaneously. Duetto serves properties from mid-scale hotels to luxury casino resorts and is particularly dominant in the Las Vegas market and among branded lifestyle hotel operators globally.',
 'https://duettocloud.com', 'https://duettocloud.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.5, 2100, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['hotel-management', 'revenue-management', 'hospitality'],
 ARRAY['Open Pricing methodology prices each room type independently for superior revenue capture', 'GameChanger engine updates rate recommendations continuously as demand signals shift', 'Integrates with all major PMS, CRS, and channel manager platforms for automated rate distribution', 'Strong track record in complex mixed-use properties including casino hotels and resorts'],
 ARRAY['Enterprise-tier pricing - not accessible for independent hotels or small properties', 'Implementation requires 2-3 months of historical data ingestion and system integration', 'Full value requires clean PMS data and well-maintained room type and rate plan structure', 'UI has a steeper learning curve than consumer-grade tools for revenue managers new to RMS'],
 ARRAY['Large hotels and resorts replacing manual rate-setting processes with AI-driven revenue management', 'Hotel chains optimising pricing across multiple properties and booking windows simultaneously', 'Revenue managers running casino hotels with complex room type and package pricing'],
 NOW()),

('revinate', 'Revinate', 'Hotel guest data platform for marketing automation, reputation management, and direct bookings',
 E'Revinate is the guest data and marketing automation platform used by hotels to convert OTA guests into direct-booking repeat customers. The core insight behind Revinate is that hotels capture enormous amounts of guest data across PMS check-in records, post-stay surveys, review sites, and email interactions - but most hotels have no system to consolidate, activate, and market to that data as a unified guest profile.\n\nRevinate''s guest data platform (GDP) creates a single guest record by merging PMS data, email engagement history, survey responses, and review data into a unified profile. The marketing automation module uses these profiles to send highly segmented email campaigns - pre-arrival upsell offers, post-stay win-back campaigns, loyalty recognition emails, and seasonal promotions - personalised at the individual guest level based on stay history, room preferences, and spending patterns.\n\nThe reputation management module aggregates guest reviews from TripAdvisor, Google, Booking.com, and Expedia into a single dashboard with AI-generated response suggestions. Operations teams can track sentiment trends across properties and identify recurring service issues before they compound. For hotel groups running multi-property operations, Revinate provides centralised visibility into guest satisfaction across all locations with the ability to drill into property-level detail.\n\nThe ROI model for Revinate is direct booking revenue recovered from OTA channels - hotels typically see 3-5x return on subscription cost through incremental direct booking revenue driven by Revinate email campaigns. Mid-market and enterprise hotel groups with 100+ rooms and meaningful past-guest data see the strongest returns from the platform.',
 'https://revinate.com', 'https://revinate.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.4, 2600, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['hospitality', 'hotel-management', 'revenue-management'],
 ARRAY['Unified guest data platform merges PMS, email, survey, and review data into single guest profiles', 'Marketing automation drives incremental direct bookings from past guests at low acquisition cost', 'Reputation management aggregates reviews from all major platforms with AI response suggestions', 'Multi-property hotel groups get centralised sentiment tracking with property-level drill-down'],
 ARRAY['Requires clean and complete PMS guest data to deliver full segmentation and personalisation value', 'Email marketing features less advanced than dedicated email platforms like Klaviyo or Mailchimp', 'Setup and data integration requires investment from both Revinate and hotel IT or operations teams', 'Subscription cost requires sufficient past-guest volume to justify through direct booking ROI'],
 ARRAY['Converting OTA bookers into direct-booking repeat guests through targeted email campaigns', 'Managing online reputation across TripAdvisor, Google, and Booking.com from a single platform', 'Personalising pre-arrival and post-stay communications based on individual guest stay history'],
 NOW()),

('navan', 'Navan', 'All-in-one business travel and expense management platform with AI-powered booking and policy',
 E'Navan (formerly TripActions) is the leading modern business travel and expense management platform, combining a corporate travel booking tool, expense management software, and corporate card program in a single integrated product. The platform is positioned as the replacement for the disconnected stack of legacy travel management companies, expense report tools, and corporate credit cards that most mid-market and enterprise companies run today.\n\nThe travel booking experience is built around the employee - a clean, consumer-quality interface where travelers can book flights, hotels, and car rentals within company policy guardrails, without the friction of legacy booking tools designed primarily for travel managers. AI features surface the most policy-compliant and cost-efficient options based on the traveler''s profile, destination, and trip dates. Policy violations are flagged inline during booking rather than discovered after the fact during expense review.\n\nNavan Expense automates the expense management workflow for non-travel spending: employees photograph receipts, AI categorises the expense and extracts merchant and amount data, and the expense is routed through the appropriate approval chain based on company policy. The corporate Navan Card captures all spending data in real time, eliminating the end-of-month receipt reconciliation process. Finance teams get real-time visibility into travel and expense spend across the organisation without waiting for monthly reports.\n\nNavan is free for travellers and operates on a model where revenue comes from supplier bookings and card interchange. This makes it particularly attractive for mid-market companies that want to modernise travel and expense management without adding a significant SaaS line item. The platform serves companies from 50 to 5,000 employees across the US, EU, and UK.',
 'https://navan.com', 'https://navan.com',
 'freemium', true, 0, 4.6, 5900, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['business-travel', 'travel', 'productivity'],
 ARRAY['Free for travelers - revenue from supplier bookings makes it accessible for cost-conscious companies', 'Consumer-quality booking UX with built-in policy guardrails and real-time compliance flagging', 'Navan Expense automates receipt capture, categorisation, and approval routing end-to-end', 'Real-time spend visibility across travel and expense for finance teams without month-end delays'],
 ARRAY['Supplier-funded model means hotel and flight inventory skews toward partners for optimal margin', 'Corporate card program requires credit underwriting - not available for all company profiles', 'International coverage and supplier network strongest in North America and Western Europe', 'Some advanced policy configuration requires dedicated implementation support'],
 ARRAY['Replacing legacy travel management companies and expense tools with a single modern platform', 'Automating employee expense reporting to eliminate monthly receipt reconciliation', 'Giving finance teams real-time visibility into travel and expense spend across the organisation'],
 NOW()),

('canary-technologies', 'Canary Technologies', 'Hotel guest management platform for digital check-in, upselling, and contactless operations',
 E'Canary Technologies is a hotel guest management platform that provides digital check-in, upselling, contactless checkout, and guest communication tools as a layer on top of the hotel''s existing property management system. Rather than replacing the PMS, Canary connects to it via API and adds a modern guest-facing experience that most legacy PMS systems cannot deliver without expensive custom development.\n\nThe digital check-in module allows guests to complete registration, upload ID, sign the registration card, and add a credit card on file from their mobile device before arrival. For hotels, this compresses check-in time at the front desk and reduces card-not-present fraud risk through AI-powered ID verification. The upselling engine presents personalised room upgrade offers, early check-in, late checkout, and add-on packages to guests during the pre-arrival window, driving incremental ancillary revenue that would otherwise require front desk staff to present manually.\n\nCanary''s guest messaging tool provides a two-way SMS and messaging interface that allows guests to communicate with the hotel from arrival through checkout without downloading an app. The AI assistant handles common inquiries - WiFi passwords, parking information, restaurant hours, checkout time - automatically, escalating complex requests to hotel staff. Contactless checkout allows guests to review their folio, settle their bill, and provide feedback from their device at departure.\n\nThe platform has processed over $1 billion in upsell revenue for hotel clients and is deployed at over 20,000 properties globally. For hotels that cannot rebuild their entire technology stack but want to offer a modern guest experience, Canary provides the guest-facing layer without requiring a PMS migration.',
 'https://canarytechnologies.com', 'https://canarytechnologies.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.6, 3100, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['hospitality', 'hotel-management', 'travel'],
 ARRAY['Layered deployment on top of existing PMS - no full technology migration required', 'AI-powered ID verification at digital check-in reduces card-not-present fraud risk', 'Upselling engine generates measurable ancillary revenue from upgrade and add-on offers', 'Two-way messaging with AI-handled common inquiries reduces front desk call volume'],
 ARRAY['Value depends heavily on PMS integration quality - some older PMS platforms have limited API access', 'Upselling revenue requires meaningful guest volume to generate ROI over subscription cost', 'Guest adoption of digital check-in varies by property type and guest demographic', 'Mobile app experience is less polished than standalone hospitality apps at the premium tier'],
 ARRAY['Hotels adding digital check-in and contactless checkout without replacing legacy PMS', 'Revenue managers automating pre-arrival upsell offers to drive ancillary revenue per guest', 'Properties reducing front desk call volume with AI-powered guest messaging and FAQ automation'],
